cabhPsDevMib.description: This MIB module supplies the basic management objects for the Portal Services logical element of a CableHome compliant Residential Gateway device. The PS device parameters describe general PS Device attributes and behavior characteristics. Most of the PS Device MIB is needed for configuration download. Copyright (C) The Internet Society (2003). This version of this MIB module is part of RFC xxxx; see the RFC itself for full legal notices.

cabhPsDevDateTime.name: cabhPsDevDateTime
cabhPsDevDateTime.description: The date and time, with optional timezone information.

cabhPsDevResetNow.name: cabhPsDevResetNow
cabhPsDevResetNow.description: Setting this object to true(1) causes the stand-alone or embedded PS device to reboot. Device code initializes as if starting from a power-on reset. The CMP ensures that MIB object values persist as specified in Appendix I of the CableHome 1.0 specification. Reading this object always returns false(2).

cabhPsDevSerialNumber.name: cabhPsDevSerialNumber
cabhPsDevSerialNumber.description: The manufacturer's serial number for this PS. This parameter is manufacturer provided and is stored in non-volatile memory.

cabhPsDevHardwareVersion.name: cabhPsDevHardwareVersion
cabhPsDevHardwareVersion.description: The manufacturer's hardware version for this PS. This parameter is manufacturer provided and is stored in non-volatile memory.

cabhPsDevWanManMacAddress.name: cabhPsDevWanManMacAddress
cabhPsDevWanManMacAddress.description: The PS WAN-Man MAC address. This is the PS hardware address to be used by the CDC to uniquely identify the PS to the cable data network DHCP server for the acquisition of an IP address to be used for management messaging between the cable network NMS and the CMP.

cabhPsDevWanDataMacAddress.name: cabhPsDevWanDataMacAddress
cabhPsDevWanDataMacAddress.description: The PS WAN-Data MAC address. The PS could have multiple WAN-Data Interfaces, which share the same hardware address. The client identifiers will be unique so that each may be assigned a different, unique IP address.

cabhPsDevTypeIdentifier.name: cabhPsDevTypeIdentifier
cabhPsDevTypeIdentifier.reference: CableHome 1.0 Specification, CH-SP-I04-030411, 7.2.3.3 CDC Requirements CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 7.3.3.2.3 CDC Function System Description
cabhPsDevTypeIdentifier.description: This is a copy of the device type identifier used in the DHCP option 60 exchanged between the PS and the DHCP server.

cabhPsDevSetToFactory.name: cabhPsDevSetToFactory
cabhPsDevSetToFactory.description: Setting this object to true(1) sets all PsDev MIB objects to the factory default values. Reading this object always returns false(2).

cabhPsDevTodSyncStatus.name: cabhPsDevTodSyncStatus
cabhPsDevTodSyncStatus.description: This object indicates whether the PS was able to successfully synchronize with the Time of Day (ToD)Server in the cable network. The PS sets this object to true(1) if the PS successfully synchronizes its time with the ToD server. The PS sets this object to false(2) if the PS does not successfully synchronize with the ToD server

cabhPsDevProvMode.name: cabhPsDevProvMode
cabhPsDevProvMode.description: This object indicates the provisioning mode in which the PS is operating. If the PS is operating in DHCP Provisioning Mode as described in the CableHome 1.1 specification, the PS sets this object to dhcpmode(1). If the PS is operating in SNMP Provisioning Mode, the PS sets this object to snmpmode(2).If the PS is not configured to operate in either dhcpmode or snmpmode it will fall back to Dormant CableHome Mode and set the value of cabhPsDevProvMode to dormantCHmode(3).

cabhPsDevLastSetToFactory.name: cabhPsDevLastSetToFactory
cabhPsDevLastSetToFactory.description: The value of sysUpTime when cabhPsDevSetToFactory was last set to true. Zero if never reset.

cabhPsDevProvisioningTimer.name: cabhPsDevProvisioningTimer
cabhPsDevProvisioningTimer.description: This object enables the user to set the duration of the provisioning timeout timer. The value is in minutes. Setting the timer to 0 disables it. The default value for the timer is 5.

cabhPsDevProvConfigFile.name: cabhPsDevProvConfigFile
cabhPsDevProvConfigFile.description: The URL of the TFTP host for downloading provisioning and configuration parameters to this device. Returns NULL if the server address is unknown.

cabhPsDevProvConfigHash.name: cabhPsDevProvConfigHash
cabhPsDevProvConfigHash.description: Hash of the contents of the config file, which is calculated and sent by the NMS to the PS. For the SHA-1 authentication algorithm the hash length is 160 bits. This hash value is encoded in the binary format.

cabhPsDevProvConfigFileStatus.name: cabhPsDevProvConfigFileStatus
cabhPsDevProvConfigFileStatus.description: This object indicates the current status of the configuration file download process. It is provided to indicate to the management entity that the PS will reject PS Configuration File triggers (set request to cabhPsDevProvConfigFile) when busy.

cabhPsDevProvConfigTLVProcessed.name: cabhPsDevProvConfigTLVProcessed
cabhPsDevProvConfigTLVProcessed.description: Number of TLVs processed in config file.

cabhPsDevProvConfigTLVRejected.name: cabhPsDevProvConfigTLVRejected
cabhPsDevProvConfigTLVRejected.description: Number of TLVs rejected in config file.

cabhPsDevProvSolicitedKeyTimeout.name: cabhPsDevProvSolicitedKeyTimeout
cabhPsDevProvSolicitedKeyTimeout.description: This timeout applies only when the Provisioning Server initiated key management (with a Wake Up message) for SNMPv3. It is the period during which the PS will save a number (inside the sequence number field) from the sent out AP Request and wait for the matching AP Reply from the Provisioning Server.

cabhPsDevProvState.name: cabhPsDevProvState
cabhPsDevProvState.description: This object indicates the completion state of the initialization process. Pass or Fail states occur after completion of the initialization flow. InProgress occurs from PS initialization start to PS initialization end.

cabhPsDevProvAuthState.name: cabhPsDevProvAuthState
cabhPsDevProvAuthState.description: This object indicates the authentication state of the configuration file.

cabhPsDevTimeServerAddrType.name: cabhPsDevTimeServerAddrType
cabhPsDevTimeServerAddrType.description: The IP address type of the Time server (RFC-868). IP version 4 is typically used.

cabhPsDevTimeServerAddr.name: cabhPsDevTimeServerAddr
cabhPsDevTimeServerAddr.description: The IP address of the Time server (RFC-868). Returns 0.0.0.0 if the time server IP address is unknown.

cabhPsDevPsDeviceType.name: cabhPsDevPsDeviceType
cabhPsDevPsDeviceType.description: The type of device, as defined in the CableHome specifications (Residential Gateway Device or CableHome Host Device), that implements this OID.

cabhPsDevPsManufacturerUrl.name: cabhPsDevPsManufacturerUrl
cabhPsDevPsManufacturerUrl.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevPsManufacturerUrl.description: Universal Resource Locator to the Residential Gateway device manufacturer's web site.

cabhPsDevPsModelUrl.name: cabhPsDevPsModelUrl
cabhPsDevPsModelUrl.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevPsModelUrl.description: Universal Resource Locator to the web site describing this CableHome compliant residential gateway device.

cabhPsDevPsModelUpc.name: cabhPsDevPsModelUpc
cabhPsDevPsModelUpc.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description. See also: Uniform Code Council www.uc-council.org
cabhPsDevPsModelUpc.description: Universal Product Code of the CableHome compliant residential gateway device.

cabhPsDevBpProfileTable.name: cabhPsDevBpProfileTable
cabhPsDevBpProfileTable.description: This table contains the information for the CableHome Host Device Profiles. Attributes of a device make up a Device Profile.

cabhPsDevBpProfileEntry.name: cabhPsDevBpProfileEntry
cabhPsDevBpProfileEntry.description: The table that describes the CableHome Host Device Profile.

cabhPsDevBpIndex.name: cabhPsDevBpIndex
cabhPsDevBpIndex.description: Integer index into the CableHome Host Device Profile Table

cabhPsDevBpDeviceType.name: cabhPsDevBpDeviceType
cabhPsDevBpDeviceType.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpDeviceType.description: The type of device, as defined by the CableHome specifications (CableHome Residential Gateway or CableHome Host Device), that passed the Device Profile whose information is made available through this table row.

cabhPsDevBpManufacturer.name: cabhPsDevBpManufacturer
cabhPsDevBpManufacturer.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpManufacturer.description: The name of the CableHome Host Device's manufacturer.

cabhPsDevBpManufacturerUrl.name: cabhPsDevBpManufacturerUrl
cabhPsDevBpManufacturerUrl.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpManufacturerUrl.description: Universal Resource Locator to the CableHome Host device manufacturer's web site.

cabhPsDevBpSerialNumber.name: cabhPsDevBpSerialNumber
cabhPsDevBpSerialNumber.description: The serial number assigned by the manufacturer for this CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpHardwareVersion.name: cabhPsDevBpHardwareVersion
cabhPsDevBpHardwareVersion.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpHardwareVersion.description: The hardware version number assigned by the manufacturer for this CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpHardwareOptions.name: cabhPsDevBpHardwareOptions
cabhPsDevBpHardwareOptions.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpHardwareOptions.description: The hardware options implemented on this CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpModelName.name: cabhPsDevBpModelName
cabhPsDevBpModelName.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpModelName.description: The model name assigned by the manufacturer for this CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpModelNumber.name: cabhPsDevBpModelNumber
cabhPsDevBpModelNumber.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpModelNumber.description: The model number assigned by the manufacturer for this CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpModelUrl.name: cabhPsDevBpModelUrl
cabhPsDevBpModelUrl.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpModelUrl.description: The Universal Resource Locator to the web site describing this CableHome Host Device model.

cabhPsDevBpModelUpc.name: cabhPsDevBpModelUpc
cabhPsDevBpModelUpc.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpModelUpc.description: Universal Product Code of the CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpModelSoftwareOs.name: cabhPsDevBpModelSoftwareOs
cabhPsDevBpModelSoftwareOs.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpModelSoftwareOs.description: Software operating system implemented on the CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpModelSoftwareVersion.name: cabhPsDevBpModelSoftwareVersion
cabhPsDevBpModelSoftwareVersion.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpModelSoftwareVersion.description: Version of the operating system implemented on the CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpLanInterfaceType.name: cabhPsDevBpLanInterfaceType
cabhPsDevBpLanInterfaceType.reference: http://www.iana.org/assignments/ianaiftype-mib See also: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description.
cabhPsDevBpLanInterfaceType.description: The ifType for the LAN Interface implemented on the CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpNumberInterfacePriorities.name: cabhPsDevBpNumberInterfacePriorities
cabhPsDevBpNumberInterfacePriorities.description: Number of QoS priorities supported by the LAN technology (Data Link Layer) implemented in the CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpPhysicalLocation.name: cabhPsDevBpPhysicalLocation
cabhPsDevBpPhysicalLocation.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpPhysicalLocation.description: Physical location of the CableHome Host Device.

cabhPsDevBpPhysicalAddress.name: cabhPsDevBpPhysicalAddress
cabhPsDevBpPhysicalAddress.reference: CableHome 1.1 Specification, CH 1.1-SP-I01-030418, 6.5.3.1.3 Device Profile Description
cabhPsDevBpPhysicalAddress.description: The CableHome Host Device's hardware address.

cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficCountersReset.name: cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficCountersReset
cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficCountersReset.description: Setting this object to clearCounters(1) resets all the traffic statistic counter entries to zero in the cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficTable. Setting this object to clearTable(2) removes all entries in the cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficTable. Reading this object always returns clearCounters(1).

cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficCountersLastReset.name: cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficCountersLastReset
cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficCountersLastReset.description: The value of sysUpTime when cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficCountersReset was last written to. Zero if never written to.

cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficEnabled.name: cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficEnabled
cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficEnabled.description: Setting this object to true(1) turns on the IP traffic counters. Setting this object false(2) turns off the IP traffic counters.

cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficTable.name: cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficTable
cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficTable.description: This table contains IP-layer Traffic Statistics for all LAN IP Devices connected to the PS.

cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficEntry.name: cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficEntry
cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficEntry.description: List of Traffic Statistics for LAN IP Devices.

cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficIndex.name: cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficIndex
cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficIndex.description: The Index into the LAN IP Traffic Statistics Table.

cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficInetAddressType.name: cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficInetAddressType
cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficInetAddressType.description: The type of IP address assigned to the LAN IP device to which the statistics in this table row apply. IP version 4 is typically used.

cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficInetAddress.name: cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficInetAddress
cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficInetAddress.description: The IP address of the LAN IP device to which the statistics in this table row apply. An IPv4 IP address is typically used.

cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficInOctets.name: cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficInOctets
cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficInOctets.description: The total number of octets received from the LAN IP address.

cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficOutOctets.name: cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficOutOctets
cabhPsDevLanIpTrafficOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted to the LAN IP address.

cabhPsDevInitTLVUnknownTrap.name: cabhPsDevInitTLVUnknownTrap
cabhPsDevInitTLVUnknownTrap.description: Event due to detection of unknown TLV during the TLV parsing process. The values of docsDevEvLevel, docsDevId, and docsDevEvText are from the entry which logs this event in the docsDevEventTable. The value of cabhPsDevWanManMacAddress indicates the WAN-Man MAC address of the PS. This part of the information is uniform across all PS Traps.

cabhPsDevInitTrap.name: cabhPsDevInitTrap
cabhPsDevInitTrap.description: This inform is issued to confirm the successful completion of the CableHome provisioning process.

cabhPsDevInitRetryTrap.name: cabhPsDevInitRetryTrap
cabhPsDevInitRetryTrap.description: An event to report a failure happened during the initialization process and was detected in the PS.

cabhPsDevDHCPFailTrap.name: cabhPsDevDHCPFailTrap
cabhPsDevDHCPFailTrap.description: An event to report the failure of a DHCP server. The value of cabhCdpServerDhcpAddressis the IP address of the DHCP server.

cabhPsDevSwUpgradeInitTrap.name: cabhPsDevSwUpgradeInitTrap
cabhPsDevSwUpgradeInitTrap.description: An event to report a software upgrade initiated event. The values of docsDevSwFilename, and docsDevSwServer indicate the software image name and the IP address of the server from which the image was downloaded.

cabhPsDevSwUpgradeFailTrap.name: cabhPsDevSwUpgradeFailTrap
cabhPsDevSwUpgradeFailTrap.description: An event to report the failure of a software upgrade attempt. The values of docsDevSwFilename, and docsDevSwServer indicate the software image name and the IP address of the server from which the image was downloaded.

cabhPsDevSwUpgradeSuccessTrap.name: cabhPsDevSwUpgradeSuccessTrap
cabhPsDevSwUpgradeSuccessTrap.description: An event to report the Software upgrade success event. The values of docsDevSwFilename, and docsDevSwServer indicate the software image name and the IP address of the server from which the image was downloaded.

cabhPsDevSwUpgradeCVCFailTrap.name: cabhPsDevSwUpgradeCVCFailTrap
cabhPsDevSwUpgradeCVCFailTrap.description: An event to report the failure of the verification of code file happened during a secure software upgrade attempt.

cabhPsDevTODFailTrap.name: cabhPsDevTODFailTrap
cabhPsDevTODFailTrap.description: An event to report the failure of a time of day server. The value of cabhPsDevTimeServerAddr indicates the server IP address.

cabhPsDevCdpWanDataIpTrap.name: cabhPsDevCdpWanDataIpTrap
cabhPsDevCdpWanDataIpTrap.description: An event to report the failure of PS to obtain all needed WAN-Data Ip Addresses. cabhCdpWanDataAddrClientId indicates the ClientId for which the failure occured.

cabhPsDevCdpThresholdTrap.name: cabhPsDevCdpThresholdTrap
cabhPsDevCdpThresholdTrap.description: An event to report that the LAN-Trans address assignment threshold has been exceeded.

cabhPsDevCspTrap.name: cabhPsDevCspTrap
cabhPsDevCspTrap.description: To report an event with the CableHome Security Portal.

cabhPsDevCapTrap.name: cabhPsDevCapTrap
cabhPsDevCapTrap.description: To report an event with the CableHome Address Portal.

cabhPsDevCtpTrap.name: cabhPsDevCtpTrap
cabhPsDevCtpTrap.description: To report an event with the CableHome Test Portal.

cabhPsDevProvEnrollTrap.name: cabhPsDevProvEnrollTrap
cabhPsDevProvEnrollTrap.description: This inform is issued to initiate the CableHome provisioning process for SNMP Provisioning Mode.

cabhPsDevCdpLanIpPoolTrap.name: cabhPsDevCdpLanIpPoolTrap
cabhPsDevCdpLanIpPoolTrap.description: An event to report that the pool of IP addresses for LAN clients, as defined by cabh CdpLanPoolStart and cabhCdpLanPoolEnd, is exhausted.

cabhPsBasicCompliance.name: cabhPsBasicCompliance
cabhPsBasicCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement the CableHome Portal Services logical element.

cabhPsDevBaseGroup.name: cabhPsDevBaseGroup
cabhPsDevBaseGroup.description: A collection of objects for providing device status and control.

cabhPsDevProvGroup.name: cabhPsDevProvGroup
cabhPsDevProvGroup.description: A collection of objects for controlling and providing status on provisioning.

cabhPsDevAttribGroup.name: cabhPsDevAttribGroup
cabhPsDevAttribGroup.description: A collection of objects for providing information on LAN IP devices known to the PS.

cabhPsDevPsStatsGroup.name: cabhPsDevPsStatsGroup
cabhPsDevPsStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects for providing information on LAN IP traffic.

cabhPsNotificationGroup.name: cabhPsNotificationGroup
cabhPsNotificationGroup.description: These notifications indicate change in status of the Portal Services set of functions in a device complying with CableLabs CableHome(tm) specifications.
